WEBVTT

00:04:29.561 --> 00:04:33.419
where people would forge their passports,
sometimes, to say that they were Jewish,

00:04:33.443 --> 00:04:35.950
because that was the only way
you could leave Russia.

00:04:35.974 --> 00:04:38.712
AG: They moved to Boston
shortly before Maria turned five.

00:04:38.736 --> 00:04:41.529
She had a lot to learn
and had to find a way to learn fast.

00:04:41.553 --> 00:04:44.069
MK: I didn't speak English at all.

00:04:44.093 --> 00:04:45.387
Just zero.

00:04:45.411 --> 00:04:49.268
And I vividly remember asking,
"How do I write my name?

00:04:49.292 --> 00:04:51.558
What do I say when I go to school?"

00:04:52.030 --> 00:04:55.649
I was really nervous because I knew
I wouldn't be able to communicate.

00:04:55.673 --> 00:04:57.752
AG: Since she couldn't
communicate verbally,

00:04:57.776 --> 00:04:59.990
Maria started paying attention
to other clues.